It's time to completely renovate the bedroom. This is the last room in the house that has only been simply decorated.
Demolish the ugly electric fireplace and stove. Seal the chimney, replace the damaged plaster, and repaint. Custom-order a wardrobe.
We usually start with a rough pencil sketch...
The messy phase is over.
A few dead birds were found behind the chimney, their bodies completely dried up : (
Get ready for the plasterers next week
Satisfied with the small niche next to it
Install the new wardrobe here (we haven't even started designing it yet 😈)
Haha, check out what we found behind the radiator!
Remember to add the cute little vent to prevent the chimney from getting damp
Install the chimney cap and chimney cover. The white storks that like to nest in the chimney should now be safer in the future 🪺
The plasterers are done. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The felt pads have been installed, and a roll of toilet paper was used as a DIY attachment for the vacuum cleaner to suck up sawdust. 😂
Part of the floor has been prepared and is ready to be laid. Let's have a cup of tea and take a break.
Well, today's progress was a bit slow because we needed to make cuts around the door frame to ensure a seamless connection with the corridor (which is also having its floor laid), and it was quite tedious. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me.
Finally, it's done, but everything is all over the place! Even worse, the instructions for assembling the new bed are terrible. Finally, I can get a good night's sleep tonight!
There's still the corridor floor and skirting boards left to do. The renovation workers are coming a month later, so we can only manage with what we have now, and the room is just bare plaster.
In the evening, I did a bit of simple DIY, using a dovetail saw and chisel to cut off part of the bottom of the door frame, so the floor could be perfectly laid underneath.
The felt padding in the corridor has also been installed.
Yesterday we also finished laying the corridor floor! We got up at 5 a.m. today to go to Heathrow Airport to collect the first parcel, then took a nap and are now finally ready to install the skirting boards in the corridor. We'll fill the joints after the glue dries.
